p: Furthermore, results obtained from the server shows that all these shortlisted compounds are active against the protease target. From the scores it can be seen that Saquinavir with score 0.40 possesses strong inhibitory effects against the proteases while the others the reported score for TCM5280805 (−0.7), TCM5280863 (−0.27), TCM5280445 (−0.22), TCM5280343 (−0.25) while TCM5458190 possess (−0.12) bioactivity score against the protease target. Thus, these results strongly suggest that the shortlisted compounds could efficiently inhibit the 3CLPro in the experimental setup and could be tested for clinical trials.
